The paper discusses the application of neural networks to reasoning tasks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the structure of neural networks and their ability to learn reasoning procedures, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper mentions several specific reasoning tasks, such as relational question answering and intuitive physics, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the design of neural architectures for complex reasoning, which is relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
